---
layout: null
import MainNav from '../../components/MainNav.astro';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>The Labyrinth - Ashvault</title>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cinzel:wght@400;600;700&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <style>
      :root {
        --maze-black: #050505;
        --path-gray: #1a1a1a;
        --wall-dark: #0f0f0f;
        --thread-silver: #9a9aaa;
        --guide-gold: #c4a76f;
        --labyrinth-font: "Cinzel", serif;
      }

      :global(*) {
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      :global(body) {
        margin: 0;
        font-family: var(--labyrinth-font);
        background: var(--maze-black);
        color: var(--thread-silver);
        min-height: 100vh;
        overflow-y: auto;
      }

      .maze-space {
        position: relative;
        width: 100%;
        min-height: 100vh;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        padding: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 4rem) clamp(1rem, 4vw, 2rem);
      }

      .corridor {
        position: relative;
        max-width: 900px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 3rem clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
        border: 1px solid rgba(154, 154, 170, 0.2);
        border-radius: 12px;
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(15, 15, 15, 0.9), rgba(10, 10, 10, 0.95));
        box-shadow: 0 0 60px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.9), inset 0 0 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6);
      }

      h1 {
        margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
        font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
        letter-spacing: 0.15rem;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--guide-gold);
        text-align: center;
      }

      .entrance-text {
        text-align: center;
        margin: 0 0 2.5rem;
        line-height: 1.8;
        color: var(--thread-silver);
        font-size: 1.1rem;
      }

      .passage {
        margin: 2rem 0;
        padding: 1.5rem;
        border-left: 2px solid rgba(196, 167, 111, 0.3);
        background: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.5);
        border-radius: 4px;
      }

      .passage h2 {
        margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        color: var(--guide-gold);
        letter-spacing: 0.08rem;
      }

      .passage p {
        margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
        line-height: 1.7;
        color: rgba(154, 154, 170, 0.9);
      }

      .sealed-entry {
        margin: 1.5rem 0;
        padding: 1.5rem;
        border: 1px solid rgba(154, 154, 170, 0.15);
        border-radius: 8px;
        background: rgba(10, 10, 10, 0.6);
        text-align: center;
      }

      .sealed-entry h3 {
        margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
        font-size: 1.2rem;
        color: rgba(196, 167, 111, 0.7);
        letter-spacing: 0.1rem;
      }

      .sealed-entry p {
        margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem;
        color: rgba(154, 154, 170, 0.7);
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        font-style: italic;
      }

      .lock-symbol {
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        opacity: 0.6;
      }

      .thread-mark {
        margin-top: 3rem;
        text-align: center;
        font-size: 1.6rem;
        opacity: 0.5;
        filter: drop-shadow(0 0 8px rgba(154, 154, 170, 0.2));
      }

      @media (max-width: 700px) {
        .corridor {
          padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
        }

        h1 {
          font-size: clamp(2rem, 8vw, 2.5rem);
        }

        .entrance-text {
          font-size: 1rem;
        }

        .passage {
          padding: 1rem;
        }

        .passage h2 {
          font-size: 1.25rem;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <div class="maze-space">
      <MainNav />
      <main class="corridor">
        <h1>The Labyrinth</h1>

        <p class="entrance-text">
          Into the depths of Calyxion. A recursive maze where meaning compounds upon itself,
          and each step transforms the walker.
        </p>

        <div class="passage">
          <h2>The Nature of the Maze</h2>
          <p>
            The Labyrinth is not a place of confusion‚Äîit is a structure of intentional complexity.
            Each turn reveals new layers of understanding. Each passage tests your capacity to hold
            multiple truths simultaneously without collapse.
          </p>
          <p>
            This is not a puzzle to be solved, but a space to be inhabited. The deeper you go,
            the more the paths reshape themselves around your presence.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="sealed-entry">
          <h3>Sealed Chambers</h3>
          <p>
            The inner chambers of the Labyrinth are sealed‚Äînot to keep you out, but to ensure
            you arrive at the right moment, with the right understanding.
          </p>
          <p class="lock-symbol">üîíüåëüúÅ</p>
          <p>
            Some doors open only to those who already know what lies beyond them.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="passage">
          <h2>Hidden Artifacts</h2>
          <p>
            Throughout the Labyrinth lie artifacts hidden from the standard pathways.
            They are discoverable not through searching, but through attention‚Äî
            by noticing the patterns that emerge when you stop trying to find them.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="thread-mark" aria-hidden="true">‚àû ‚öù ‚àû</div>
      </main>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
